{
  "doc_id": "30688",
  "text": "The level of DNA methylation at D4Z4 approximately correlates inversely with disease severity and penetrance [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Furthermore, independent of FSHD status, shorter arrays on either 4q or 10q have lower methylation levels [CITATION_3] . This was studied in detail using a methylation-sensitive FseI site in the proximal repeat unit (known to be representative of methylation across the entire array) to investigate the correlation between array length and methylation in a large study containing 254 controls, 186 FSHD1 individuals and 74 SMCHD1 mutation carriers [CITATION_4] . Note that FSHD2 shows digenic inheritance and SMCHD1 mutation carriers only develop FSHD2 if they also carry a relatively short permissive 4qA allele [CITATION_5] .",
